text:
I would say one of the best otak otak i have tasted, not your usual  otak otak (grilled fish cake made of ground fish meat mixed with tapioca starch and spices).

This otak otak has fish chunks marinated with spice paste and mixed with grated coconut.
Its has a mildly spicy flavour with flavour of coconut and. The coconut adds a gritty texture. Worth a try.

I highly recommend people stay away from this shop, the two owners Junaidah & Murset are both big time con-artist, its lucky that both this jokers are not arrested.

There is a reason why they keep shifting shops all around the island (Geylang to Engku Aman to Marine Parade to Chinatown and now Bedok) and that is because they go around renting stalls from NEA and not paying, subsequently being evicted and charged, then the started being joint operators of various hawker stall, refuse to pay their utilities & their share of the rental and in the end they run off.
The food is tasty. Simple dish but in a different way, it’s just awesome. She’s always smiling to customers.
